(1763,	1,	'2015-03-22 16:56:33',	'2015-03-22 16:56:33',	'Payment, Cancellation and Refund Policy\r\n &nbsp;\r\nIntelli Training ltd (IT)\r\n &nbsp;\r\nEffective Date: 1st November 2014\r\n &nbsp;\r\nCourses and exam fees are payable in advance and should be paid at least 5 Business days prior to taking a course. All prices quoted exclude VAT. Intelli Training (IT) Ltd is not currently registered for VAT and as such does not charge VAT on invoices. The company may become VAT registered at any point and as such would charge VAT (currently 20%) on all invoices. Customers will be given the option for a full refund if they booked a course(s) before the company was VAT registered, but were not invoiced until after the company was VAT registered.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nPayments can be made via Bank Transfer, using all major credit cards on the website, or through Paypal. Payments on the website are processed using Stripe and PayPal.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nIT endeavours to run all the courses on the dates advertised. However, if there are less than four people enrolled on a course IT reserve the right to cancel the course, provided customers are given a minimum of 10 Business days notice. In the event of cancellation customers are eligible for a full refund or to attend another course without charge.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nCancellation & Re-booking Policy\r\n &nbsp;\r\nIT endeavours to run all the courses on the dates advertised. However, if there are less than four people enrolled on a course IT reserve the right to cancel the course, provided customers are given a minimum of 10 Business days notice. In the event of cancellation customers are eligible for a full refund or to attend another course without charge.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nCustomers reserve the right to cancel or book onto another course date, although fees may apply . Customers failing to attend a course without informing IT at least 2 Business days before the course start date will also be charged the full course fee.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nCustomers that would like to cancel or reschedule course bookings more than 10 business days from a course start date will incur no cancellation or rescheduling fees.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nIf a customer would like to cancel a course booking less than 10 days before the course start date, the following fees apply:\r\n&nbsp;\r\n \r\n•	6-10 business days before the course start date: 50% of course fee.\r\n•	0-5 business days before the course start date: 100% of course fee.\r\n \r\nIf a customer would like to re-schedule a course booking less than 10 business days prior to the course start date:\r\n\r\n &nbsp;\r\n•	6-10 business days before the course start date: £100 + VAT\r\n•	0-5 business days before the course start date: £120 + VAT\r\n \r\nAll course cancellations and re-scheduling must be confirmed by email to info@bluerhinotraining.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nDiploma Package\r\n &nbsp;\r\nCustomers enrolled on the Diploma Package must have paid the full balance for the diploma package before taking their first course. Customers may seek a refund on the diploma package without charge, provided it is not less than 10 business days from the start of their first course. The same fees detailed above also apply to the diploma package.If a customer would like to cancel the diploma package and would only like to do a subset of the courses, they will be liable for the full price of any courses already taken. The diploma package offers a special discount for customers and moving to taking individual courses would revoke this discount. The customer would only be eligible for a refund on the price of the diploma package minus the full course fees (as if taken individually) of the courses already taken.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nPersonal Belongings – Loss/Damage/Theft\r\n &nbsp;\r\nPersonal belongings and items belonging to or in the possession of the Customer or Delegate brought onto IT courses are the sole responsibility of the owner and IT accepts no responsibility for the loss/damage or theft of such items.\r\n &nbsp;\r\nCopyright\r\n &nbsp;\r\nCopyright and all intellectual property rights for all Course Materials shall remain the property of IT. The Customer agrees not to reproduce, sell, hire, photograph or copy Course Materials (in whole or in part) and not to use such materials except for the purposes of post course reference or as specifically agreed with IT.\r\n \r\n ',	'Terms & Conditions',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'1403-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-03-22 16:56:33',	'2015-03-22 16:56:33',	'',	1403,	'http://www.bluerhinotraining.com/1403-revision-v1/',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
